

SUBJ:  Frame formats for X.25/X.75 LAPB modulo 128

DATE:  July 10, 1988

WRITTEN BY:  James Wang  

======================================================



1. CCITT 1984 -- Modulo 128, LAPB

  a. ****Standard formats for both x.25/x.75

          Format     Command     --hex coding------
                     Response    1st-byte  2nd-byte
         -------     --------    --------  --------
      Infor xfer      I          even      even or odd(p)
      Supervisory     RR         01        enen or odd(p/f)
           "          RNR        05        even or odd(p/f)
           "          REJ        09        even or odd(p/f)
      Unnumbered      SABME      6F/7F(p)  none
           "          DISC       43/53(p)  none
           "          FRMR       87/97(f)  none
           "          UA         63/73(f)  none
           "          DM         0F/1F(f)  none

  b. ****The following alternative formats can be used for x.75 for 
         interim period. (CCITT Table 6/x.75, Rec. X.75 page 163 note 2)

          Format     Command     --hex coding------
                     Response    1st-byte  2nd-byte
         -------     --------    --------  --------
      Infor xfer      I          even      even or odd(p)
      Supervisory     RR         01        enen or odd(p/f)
           "          RNR        05        even or odd(p/f)
           "          REJ        09        even or odd(p/f)
      Unnumbered      SABME      6F        00 or 01(p)
           "          DISC       43        00 or 01(p)
           "          FRMR       87        00 or 01(f)
           "          UA         63        00 or 01(f)
           "          DM         0F        00 or 01(f)

  
     Where: p/f stands for poll/final bit on.

==========================================================================

2. Tymnet X.25/X.75 -- Frame formats for modulo 128, LAPB.  (version 3.01, 4.03)

   a. X.75 supports CCITT's alternative formats.

   b. X.25 supports nonstandard, x.75-style, extended format.

3. Patch for XCOM to use CCITT standard format as stated in 1.a.
